&lt;h1&gt;Care Coordinator – Home Care Operations&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;$26–$30/hour + Full Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remote (Must live in California) | Full-Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tandem Care is hiring a &lt;strong&gt;Care Coordinator&lt;/strong&gt; to support our &lt;strong&gt;Continuous Care (CC) division&lt;/strong&gt;—our highest-touch, most operationally complex service line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a traditional care management role focused primarily on assessments and check-ins. This is a fast-paced operational position that requires exceptional organization, strong judgment, and the ability to make decisions quickly while balancing the needs of clients, families, and caregivers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Continuous Care clients receive dedicated, ongoing care ranging from 10 hours per week to 24/7 coverage. Because of that, this role is heavily focused on&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;staffing execution, schedule management, service recovery, caregiver accountability, and keeping care running smoothly despite the inevitable curveballs that come with home care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you thrive on solving problems, thinking three steps ahead, and bringing order to chaos, you&#39;ll fit right in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for an assigned caseload of Continuous Care clients and families&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build and maintain caregiver schedules for ongoing cases, ensuring consistency and continuity whenever possible&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Respond to caregiver call-outs, schedule disruptions, and urgent coverage needs in real time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinate replacement coverage quickly while maintaining a positive client experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Match caregivers to clients based on personality, skillset, availability, and family preferences&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Conduct client onboarding calls and prepare caregivers thoroughly for new assignments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coach caregivers on client-specific expectations, care plans, and performance concerns&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage client concerns, complaints, and service recovery situations with professionalism and urgency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proactively check in with families to identify changes in needs before they become larger problems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate closely with Recruiting, HR, Sales, and Leadership to ensure staffing pipelines support client demand&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Review caregiver visit notes and identify trends, gaps, or opportunities for improvement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Document all communication, schedule changes, client updates, and action items accurately and consistently&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Think critically and make judgment calls independently while escalating concerns appropriately&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What This Job Actually Feels Like&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some days will go exactly as planned.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most won&#39;t.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A caregiver calls out thirty minutes before a shift. A family requests schedule changes. A client is discharged unexpectedly from rehab. Someone needs to be staffed immediately. A caregiver isn&#39;t the right fit. A family needs reassurance. Another client needs an additional overnight shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll pivot constantly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll prioritize dozens of moving pieces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll make decisions quickly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And you&#39;ll have the satisfaction of knowing that because of your work, vulnerable seniors remain safe at home and families can breathe a little

&lt;h2 data-start=&quot;270&quot; data-end=&quot;345&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Now Hiring: Day Shift Caregivers for Long-Term, Consistent Assignments&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
